ABUJA – President Muhammadu Buhari has called on nurses, midwives and all healthcare professionals to work together to protect and restore, where need be, the health of Nigerians. He said: “My administration places priority on the health of citizens as a cornerstone of human capital development and will continue to ensure that healthcare is always positioned as a focus of our next level agenda.” He made this known on Thursday at the official launch of Nursing Now Campaign in Nigeria, an initiative of the World Health Organisation (WHO) and the International Council of Nurses, aimed at raising the profile and status of nursing worldwide. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The president, who was represented at the occasion by the Minister of Health, Dr. Osagie Ehanire, said his administration initiated the Basic Health Care Provision Fund (BHCPF), a flagship programme to ensure that vulnerable Nigerians got access to quality and affordable service delivery towards the attainment of Universal Health Coverage (UHC).